The virus has also spread in Guinea, Sierra Leone and Nigeria.
In total, more than 1500 people have already died, and thousands more have become infected.
Foreign companies withdraw employees
Companies are suspending their operations everywhere in the resource-rich countries.
Foreign companies such as the steel company Arcelor Mittal are pulling off their employees, several international airlines are no longer flying to the affected regions.
The local traders and farmers are also reacting: only a few merchants still leave their hometowns to get supplies.
