In the markets, the stockpile of basic foodstuffs such as rice is dwindling.
At the same time, the region, which is heavily dependent on international companies, is in danger of image damage - with far-reaching consequences.
The biggest danger is that international companies basically avoid the area for a long time, says Philippe Hugon of the French think tank Iris.
