The disease also weighs on the already strained state budgets of the affected states.
Credit rating agency Moody's fears their budgets will be heavily strained by the high spending on the health care system and, in addition, by the deteriorating economy.
The African Development Bank has already promised to help out the health systems of the affected countries with $60 million (€45 million).
